# Adversarial line-by-line review — CONSULT-41 door-snap fix

Scope: mechanical correctness only (not narrow-gap / blast-radius for Change A).

---

## Change A — `FloorMesh.cpp` `continue` on `PWR_WalkOk`

**Verdict: Mechanically correct** (given the locked invariant `centerWalk == PWR_WalkOk` ⇒ spurious seam contact).

### `continue` target
The `continue` sits inside the per-triangle **edge** loop (`for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++)`), in the `else` of `canExitEdge(...)` (uncrossable branch):

```2855:2866:src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp
			else
			{
				// ---- Door-snap fix (avatar floor-seam rubberband) ----
				// ...
				if(centerWalkResult == PWR_WalkOk)
				{
					continue;
				}
```

`continue` advances to the **next edge** of the same triangle, not the outer `while (!unprocessed.empty())` — correct for “skip recording this edge’s circle contact, keep scanning.”

### `centerWalkResult` scope / validity
Declared and assigned before the queue walk; early returns prevent use uninitialized:

```2731:2756:src/engine/shared/library/sharedCollision/src/shared/core/FloorMesh.cpp
	PathWalkResult centerWalkResult;
	float centerHitTime = REAL_MAX;
	// ...
	{
		centerWalkResult = pathWalkPoint( startLoc, delta, centerHitTriId, centerHitEdge, centerHitTime );

		if(    (centerWalkResult == PWR_MissedStartTri) 
			|| (centerWalkResult == PWR_CantEnter) 
			|| (centerWalkResult == PWR_WalkFailed) 
			|| (centerWalkResult == PWR_StartLocInvalid) )
		{
			return centerWalkResult;
		}
		else if( centerWalkResult == PWR_InContact )
		{
			// ...
			return PWR_CenterInContact;
		}
```

By the time the edge loop runs (2793+), `centerWalkResult` is always defined. `PWR_WalkOk` is a stable scalar for the whole call — not per-edge.

### Line-level logic
- Only runs when `canExitEdge(...)` is **false** (uncrossable) — crossable edges take the neighbor-push branch at 2844–2853, never hit this `continue`.
- Suppressed edges do not set `circleHitTime` / `hitAnything`; other edges and triangles are still evaluated — no accidental early exit from the walk.
- Consistent with downstream `!hitAnything` + `centerWalkResult == PWR_WalkOk` → `PWR_WalkOk` at 3044–3053.

**No line-level bug found** under the locked seam-contact model.

---

## Change B — pull-in rate limit (`FreeChaseCamera.cpp`)

**Verdict: Correct for the measured door-snap (stable `m_zoom`, collision-only drop); incorrect as written for general third-person zoom-in.**

### `zoomAtFrameStart` capture point

```603:605:src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/camera/FreeChaseCamera.cpp
	float const zoomAtFrameStart = m_currentZoom; // door-snap fix: last frame's rendered zoom, for the inward pull-in rate limit below

	m_currentZoom = linearInterpolate (m_currentZoom, m_zoom, ms_cameraZoomSpeed);
```

- Captured **before** recovery lerp — matches comment (“last frame’s rendered zoom”).
- Nothing writes `m_currentZoom` between 603 and 605.
- `zoomAtFrameStart` itself is never mutated.

### Uses of `m_currentZoom` between capture and clamp

| Line | Op | Notes |
|------|-----|-------|
| 605 | write | recovery lerp toward `m_zoom` |
| 661 | read | shoulder-ray gate (`>= scaledFirstPersonDistance`) — pre-collision |
| 679 | read | early first-person branch — pre-collision |
| 698 / 746 | write | collision pull-in (the snap being fixed) |
| 756–759 | read/write | rate limit |

Nothing **reads** the unlimited post-collision value before the clamp runs. Shoulder block and early first-person use pre-collision zoom only (pre-existing ordering, not introduced by this diff).

### Interaction with first-person checks

Two checks:

```679:682:src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/camera/FreeChaseCamera.cpp
	if (m_currentZoom < scaledFirstPersonDistance)
	{
		setFirstPerson (true);
	}
```

```762:765:src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/camera/FreeChaseCamera.cpp
		if (m_currentZoom < scaledFirstPersonDistance)
			setFirstPerson (true);
		else
			move_o (Vector::negativeUnitZ * m_currentZoom);
```

- Rate limit runs **after** collision, **before** the second check — correct ordering for “ease pull-in, then decide first-person.”
- Rate limit can **delay** first-person entry when collision would have snapped below threshold in one frame — intentional per locked trade-off.
- Early check at 679 can still force first-person **before** collision/rate-limit run; that path pre-dates this fix.

### Bug: baseline includes recovery lerp, not just collision

Rate limit:

```756:759:src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/camera/FreeChaseCamera.cpp
			float const maxPullIn = elapsedTime * cs_cameraPullInSpeed;
			if (m_currentZoom < zoomAtFrameStart - maxPullIn)
				m_currentZoom = zoomAtFrameStart - maxPullIn;
```

It runs **every third-person frame** (inside the `else` of 679), **whether or not** collision fired.

Default `ms_cameraZoomSpeed = 0.2` (`ConfigClientGame.cpp:1122`). When `m_zoom < m_currentZoom` (user zooming in), recovery lerp at 605 often pulls in **far more** than `8 m/s × dt`:

- Example: `zoomAtFrameStart = 10`, `m_zoom = 3`, `dt = 0.016`  
  - After lerp: `8.6` (−1.4 m)  
  - Rate-limit floor: `10 − 0.128 = 9.872`  
  - **`m_currentZoom` is raised to 9.872`** — recovery lerp partially undone.

For any `zoomAtFrameStart > ~3.6 m` with default lerp, inward recovery exceeds 8 m/s and the clamp triggers **every frame**. Net effect: **all third-person zoom-in is capped at 8 m/s**, not just collision pull-in. Pop-out is unaffected (condition only fires on decrease below baseline).

Door-snap case (stable zoom, lerp ≈ no-op, big collision drop): works as intended.

**Suggested fix:** anchor to pre-collision zoom, not pre-lerp:

```cpp
// After line 605 (or immediately before the collision block at ~687):
float const zoomBeforeCollision = m_currentZoom;

// ... collision assigns m_currentZoom ...

float const maxPullIn = elapsedTime * cs_cameraPullInSpeed;
if (m_currentZoom < zoomBeforeCollision - maxPullIn)
    m_currentZoom = zoomBeforeCollision - maxPullIn;
```

Optionally skip the clamp when `!m_colliding && !hit` if you only want to ease wall hits.

### `elapsedTime` spike (e.g. 0.5 s hitch)

`maxPullIn = 0.5 × 8 = 4.0 m` — a measured ~2.1 m door snap passes through unclamped. Same frame, Change C’s shoulder alpha also hits `1.0` (instant zero).

Acceptable as a hitch edge case if hitches are rare; if not, cap delta:

```cpp
float const maxPullIn = std::min(elapsedTime * cs_cameraPullInSpeed, cs_cameraPullInSpeed * 0.05f); // e.g. 0.4 m max
```

